      "id": "story-002",
      "type": "pasted",
      "title": "Character: The Seeker",
      "content": "## THE SEEKER - Player Character\n\n### Overview\nThe player character, known only as \"The Seeker,\" is a being formed from countless lost memories. Neither fully alive nor truly dead, they exist in a liminal state between what was and what might be.\n\n### Visual Design\n- Humanoid silhouette, features obscured by a cowl or hood\n- Body seems to shimmer with fragments of memories\n- Eyes glow with soft, shifting colors\n- Wears tattered robes that trail into mist\n- Gender ambiguous - players can project their own identity\n\n### Personality\nThe Seeker speaks rarely, and when they do, their voice echoes with hints of many others:\n\n> *\"I remember... fragments. A child's laughter. A warrior's last breath. A lover's whisper. All of them are me. None of them are me.\"*\n\n### Motivation\n- Primary: Reach the Heart of the Void to learn the truth of their existence\n- Secondary: Piece together whose memories they carry\n- Hidden: Discover if they can ever truly \"be\" someone again\n\n### Arc Across Runs\nEach run reveals more fragments of the Seeker's origin. By the time players defeat the final boss, they should understand:\n1. The Seeker was once a real person\n2. They chose to become this to save others\n3. The sacrifice cost them their identity\n4. Victory might mean letting go forever",
      "createdAt": "2026-01-09T14:00:00Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-01-28T10:00:00Z"
