      "id": "story-003",
      "type": "pasted",
      "title": "The Void Lore",
      "content": "## THE VOID - Core Mythology\n\n### What Is The Void?\nThe Void is not empty space. It is anti-existence—a force that consumes not just matter, but meaning itself. When the Void touches something, that thing doesn't just cease to exist; it becomes as if it never existed at all.\n\n### Origins\nThe Void predates the universe. Some scholars theorized it was what existed \"before\" creation—the default state of reality that consciousness pushed back against. When enough minds gathered, they created light, matter, and meaning. But the Void never stopped pushing back.\n\n### The Hunger\nThe Void is not sentient in any way we understand. It doesn't hate life—it simply exists in opposition to it. Like water seeking its level, the Void constantly presses against the boundaries of reality, seeking to reclaim what was \"stolen\" from it.\n\nHowever, some survivors claim the Void has... echoes. Patterns of behavior that suggest something within it remembers what it has consumed.\n\n### The Corruption\nWhen memories or beings resist consumption, they sometimes become \"corrupted\" instead of destroyed. These corrupted entities serve the Void, hunting down other survivors. They are tragic figures—fragments of who they once were, twisted into weapons against everything they loved.\n\n### The Memory Fragments\nNot all consumed memories are destroyed. Some survive as crystallized shards of pure recollection. These Memory Fragments contain power—the power of experience, emotion, and will. The Seeker can collect and wield these fragments as weapons against the Void.\n\n*But using the memories of the dead raises its own moral questions...*",
      "createdAt": "2026-01-10T09:00:00Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-01-29T11:45:00Z"
    },
