      "id": "story-004",
      "type": "pasted",
      "title": "Event: The Crying Child",
      "content": "## EVENT: The Crying Child\n\n**Sector:** 1-2 (Early game)\n**Mood:** Melancholic, mysterious\n\n---\n\n### SCENE DESCRIPTION\n*You find a small figure huddled in the shadow of a broken monolith. As you approach, you realize it's not quite a child—more like the memory of one. It flickers like a candle flame, and you can see stars through its translucent form.*\n\n*It looks up at you with eyes that hold centuries of loneliness.*\n\n**CHILD:** You... you can see me?\n\n---\n\n### CHOICE 1: \"Yes. I see you.\"\n\n**CHILD:** No one has seen me in so long. I've been waiting here since... since...\n\n*The child's form wavers, struggling to remember.*\n\n**CHILD:** I was waiting for my mother. She told me to wait here. But the sky broke open, and... and...\n\n**[SUB-CHOICE A: \"She's gone. I'm sorry.\"]**\n- Child fades peacefully, leaving behind a Memory Fragment (Rare Card)\n- Gain: \"Mother's Warmth\" - Block 12, gain 1 Energy next turn\n- *Sometimes the kindest truth is a gentle ending.*\n\n**[SUB-CHOICE B: \"I'll help you find her.\"]**\n- Child follows you for 3 combats, occasionally blocking damage\n- After 3 combats, child realizes truth on their own, departs peacefully\n- Gain: \"Childlike Wonder\" - Draw 2 cards, costs 0 this combat only\n\n---\n\n### CHOICE 2: \"I don't have time for this.\"\n\n*The child's face crumples. Their form flickers more violently.*\n\n**CHILD:** Everyone says that. Everyone leaves.\n\n- Take 5 damage (guilt manifesting as self-harm)\n- Void Meter +10%\n- *Some memories persist through spite alone.*\n\n---\n\n### CHOICE 3: [VOID PATH] \"Your mother sent me. Come with me.\"\n\n*The lie comes easily. Too easily. The child's face lights up with desperate hope.*\n\n**CHILD:** Really?! She remembered me?\n\n- Gain: \"Corrupted Innocence\" (Void Card) - Deal 15 damage. Gain 2 Corruption.\n- Void Meter +20%\n- *The sweetest lies taste like poison on the soul.*\n\n---\n\n**DESIGN NOTES:**\n- This event establishes the tone: melancholic but not gratuitously dark\n- Players should feel the weight of their choices\n- The \"kind\" options aren't necessarily the \"best\" gameplay options\n- Void path should be tempting but clearly morally compromised",
      "createdAt": "2026-01-15T16:00:00Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-02-01T14:20:00Z"
    },
