      "id": "story-005",
      "type": "pasted",
      "title": "Boss: The Hollow King",
      "content": "## BOSS: THE HOLLOW KING\n\n**Sector:** End of Sector 2\n**Theme:** Forgotten royalty, corrupted duty\n\n---\n\n### VISUAL DESCRIPTION\nOnce a king of a vast empire, now a towering figure of corroded armor and crystallized regret. His crown floats above an empty helm. Where his face should be, there is only a swirling void occasionally lit by the ghosts of his subjects.\n\nHis cape is made of tattered banners from his kingdom. If you look closely, you can see tiny figures trapped in the fabric, still going about their daily lives in endless loops.\n\n---\n\n### PERSONALITY\nThe Hollow King speaks in the royal \"we,\" but his voice carries the weight of millions.\n\n> *\"We stood against the Void. We gathered our armies, our mages, our heroes. We promised our people they would be safe.\"*\n\n> *\"We lied.\"*\n\n> *\"Now we are all that remains. Their king. Their failure. Their tomb.\"*\n\n---\n\n### MECHANICAL IDENTITY\n- **Phase 1:** Defensive, builds Block (representing his protector role)\n- **Phase 2:** Summons \"Loyal Subjects\" (weak enemies that buff him when killed)\n- **Phase 3:** Goes on offensive, attacks become desperate and erratic\n\n**Special Mechanic: \"Weight of the Crown\"**\n- At start of each turn, Hollow King gains Strength equal to the number of Loyal Subjects that have died\n- Creates a moral tension: killing his subjects makes him stronger, but leaving them alive means chip damage\n\n---\n\n### DEATH DIALOGUE\n\n*As the final blow lands, the Hollow King's armor crumbles. The void within him spills outward, taking the shape of thousands of faces—his subjects, finally released.*\n\n**HOLLOW KING:** We... we can rest now?\n\n*A moment of peace crosses what remains of his features.*\n\n**HOLLOW KING:** Tell us... was there anything left worth protecting?\n\n**[Player Response - affects epilogue]:**\n- \"Yes. I'm still here.\"\n- \"I don't know anymore.\"\n- *[Silence]*\n\n---\n\n**MUSIC NOTES:**\n- Phase 1: Solemn orchestral, emphasis on strings\n- Phase 2: Add choir (representing subjects), builds tension\n- Phase 3: Discordant, desperate, tempo increases\n- Death: Music fades to single piano note, then silence",
      "createdAt": "2026-01-18T11:30:00Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-01-30T16:00:00Z"
