      "id": "story-006",
      "type": "pasted",
      "title": "Ending: True Ending Draft",
      "content": "## TRUE ENDING - \"Echoes Eternal\"\n\n*Unlocked by: Completing all Memory Bond chains, sparing the Hollow King's subjects, choosing \"I see you\" for the Crying Child*\n\n---\n\n### THE HEART OF THE VOID\n\n*The Seeker stands at the center of everything and nothing. The Heart of the Void pulses before them—not with malice, but with an ancient, terrible loneliness.*\n\n**VOID (speaking for the first time):**\n*...you came.*\n\n**SEEKER:** You can speak?\n\n**VOID:** *Through what I've consumed. Through the echoes. Through you.*\n\n*The Seeker sees visions: the Void before creation, existing in perfect, empty silence. Then the first light. The first thought. The first memory.*\n\n**VOID:** *I did not choose to be this. When consciousness was born, I became its opposite. I hunger because you dream. I consume because you create. I am the price of existence.*\n\n**SEEKER:** Then why fight? Why resist you?\n\n**VOID:** *Because that is what makes you beautiful.*\n\n*The Heart opens, revealing a choice.*\n\n---\n\n### FINAL CHOICE\n\n**OPTION A: \"End the cycle.\"**\n- The Seeker merges with the Void, becoming its new Heart\n- Their consciousness spreads through the consumed memories\n- They become a guardian, giving the dead peace instead of oblivion\n- Bittersweet: The Seeker loses themselves, but saves everyone\n\n**OPTION B: \"There has to be another way.\"**\n- The Seeker refuses to accept the binary\n- Uses accumulated Memory Bonds to forge a new path\n- The Void and consciousness learn to coexist\n- Hopeful: Harder to achieve, but suggests change is possible\n\n---\n\n### FINAL MONOLOGUE (Both endings)\n\n*The screen fades to the same starfield from the opening. But now, the stars are brighter. The Void is still there, but it no longer reaches.*\n\n**NARRATOR (the Seeker's voice, now):**\nI used to wonder whose memories I carried. Whose life I was living. Whose story I was finishing.\n\n*Fragments of every character we've met flash by—the Crying Child, the Hollow King, the countless faces in the Void.*\n\n**NARRATOR:**\nNow I understand. They were never separate. Every memory is connected. Every echo carries forward. Every ending is a beginning.\n\n*A new figure forms from scattered light. A new Seeker. A new run.*\n\n**NARRATOR:**\nAnd somewhere, in the space between what was and what will be...\n\n*The title appears one final time: ECHOES OF THE VOID*\n\n**NARRATOR:**\n...we remember.\n\n**FADE TO BLACK.**\n\n---\n\n**CREDITS MUSIC:** Gentle reprise of main theme, now with choir\n**POST-CREDITS TEASE:** The Void speaks one more word: *\"...thank you.\"*",
